fields.name: version
fields.comments: The version

fields.name: checkout_strategy
fields.comments: default will be a safe checkout

fields.name: disable_filters
fields.comments: don't apply filters like CRLF conversion

fields.name: dir_mode
fields.comments: default is 0755

fields.name: file_mode
fields.comments: default is 0644 or 0755 as dictated by blob

fields.name: file_open_flags
fields.comments: default is O_CREAT | O_TRUNC | O_WRONLY

fields.name: notify_flags
fields.comments: see `git_checkout_notify_t` above

fields.name: notify_cb
fields.comments: Optional callback to get notifications on specific file states.

fields.name: notify_payload
fields.comments: Payload passed to notify_cb

fields.name: progress_cb
fields.comments: Optional callback to notify the consumer of checkout progress.

fields.name: progress_payload
fields.comments: Payload passed to progress_cb

fields.name: paths
fields.comments:
A list of wildmatch patterns or paths.

 By default, all paths are processed. If you pass an array of wildmatch
 patterns, those will be used to filter which paths should be taken into
 account.

 Use GIT_CHECKOUT_DISABLE_PATHSPEC_MATCH to treat as a simple list.

fields.name: baseline
fields.comments:
The expected content of the working directory; defaults to HEAD.

 If the working directory does not match this baseline information,
 that will produce a checkout conflict.

fields.name: baseline_index
fields.comments:
Like `baseline` above, though expressed as an index.  This
 option overrides `baseline`.

fields.name: target_directory
fields.comments: alternative checkout path to workdir

fields.name: ancestor_label
fields.comments: the name of the common ancestor side of conflicts

fields.name: our_label
fields.comments: the name of the "our" side of conflicts

fields.name: their_label
fields.comments: the name of the "their" side of conflicts

fields.name: perfdata_cb
fields.comments: Optional callback to notify the consumer of performance data.

fields.name: perfdata_payload
fields.comments: Payload passed to perfdata_cb

fields.name: disabled_filters
fields.comments: A list filters to disable during checkout.
